    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "Imam al-Sadiq (AS) teaches that to have one's fast accepted by God, one should conclude it with a righteous saying or deed. When asked to specify, he explains that the righteous saying is the shahada (testimony of faith: 'there is no god but Allah'), and the righteous action is paying zakat al-fitra, the obligatory alms given at the end of Ramadan before Eid prayer. This hadith connects the spiritual discipline of fasting with both verbal devotion and charitable action, reflecting the Shi'a emphasis on combining faith with deeds.",
        "key_terms": {
          "صيام": "Fasting (siyam) — abstaining from food, drink, and other things from dawn to sunset during Ramadan",
          "شهادة": "Testimony (shahada) — the declaration that there is no god but Allah",
          "الفطرة": "Zakat al-Fitra — obligatory alms given at the end of Ramadan, typically one sa' of staple food per household member"
        },
        "seo_question": "What did Imam al-Sadiq say about completing fasting with a good saying and good action?"
      },
      "ur": {
        "summary": "امام صادق (علیہما السلام) فرماتے ہیں کہ روزے کو شہادت اور زکات الفطر سے ختم کرنا چاہیے۔",
        "key_terms": {
          "صيام": "روزہ — رمضان میں طلوع فجر سے غروب آفتاب تک پرہیز",
          "شهادة": "شہادت — لا الہ الا اللہ کا اعلان",
          "الفطرة": "زکات الفطر — رمضان کے آخر میں ادا کیا جانے والا صدقہ"
        },
        "seo_question": "امام صادق نے روزے کو نیک قول اور عمل سے ختم کرنے کے بارے میں کیا فرمایا؟"
      },
